%o A007953 /* The next few PARI programs are kept for historical and pedagogical reasons.
%o A007953    For practical use, the suggested and most efficient code is: A007953=sumdigits */
%o A007953 (PARI) a(n)=if(n<1, 0, if(n%10, a(n-1)+1, a(n/10))) \\ Recursive, very inefficient. A more efficient recursive variant: a(n)=if(n>9, n=divrem(n, 10); n[2]+a(n[1]), n)
%o A007953 (PARI) a(n, b=10)={my(s=(n=divrem(n, b))[2]); while(n[1]>=b, s+=(n=divrem(n[1], b))[2]); s+n[1]} \\ _M. F. Hasler_, Mar 22 2011
%o A007953 (PARI) a(n)=sum(i=1, #n=digits(n), n[i]) \\ Twice as fast. Not so nice but faster:
%o A007953 (PARI) a(n)=sum(i=1,#n=Vecsmall(Str(n)),n[i])-48*#n \\ _M. F. Hasler_, May 10 2015
%o A007953 /* Since PARI 2.7, one can also use: a(n)=vecsum(digits(n)), or better: A007953=sumdigits. [Edited and commented by _M. F. Hasler_, Nov 09 2018] */
%o A007953 (PARI) a(n) = sumdigits(n); \\ _Altug Alkan_, Apr 19 2018
